    "analysis": "From the previous Executor run (summary provided), metric data is populated and the 'carts' service stands out with high P95 for memory (~2.15e8) and socket (~11.74). trace.csv and error_logs.csv were empty, and log.csv contains log.row_count and log.error_count groups with no obvious error_count in the top groups. To follow the diagnosis workflow, we must: 1) compute global thresholds (P95 and for logs also P15) using the full series for each component-KPI (restricted to candidate services: carts, catalogue, orders, payment, user), and 2) filter the raw telemetry to the incident window 2024-01-20 10:47:52 to 2024-01-20 11:17:52 UTC and detect anomalies relative to those global thresholds. Traces and error logs are empty so metrics and logs are the primary sources. Next step is to detect metric anomalies (>=P95) within the incident window for the candidate services and to detect log anomalies: low traffic (log.row_count <= P15) or elevated errors (log.error_count >= P95) within the same window. The result should be compact aggregates per component-KPI showing counts, earliest/latest anomaly timestamps, max (or min) anomaly value, and the precomputed threshold. This will narrow down faulty components for further fault identification.",
